-MoFjVT7tS5e25Nu-Cus.text: Incident reported at 3111 Upton Ave N.

-MoFjVhI22JnRsSG8Y_u.text: Firefighters confirm a shed attached to a house has caught fire. They advise the fire is extending to the house.

-MoFjc_9Vq9BtbO2QOtb.text: Firefighters are working to establish a water supply source to attack the blaze.

-MoFkPgAzIPplXIHAM9Q.text: Firefighters report the blaze on the detached shed is spreading to the exposure of the nearby two-story home. They are searching for possible extensions from the shed fire.

-MoFkXimOnmKMqn7o0Kn.text: Firefighters confirm there are no flames on both floors inside the residence.

-MoFlCnjAIcHMRE5a4y1.text: Firefighters advise Lowry Ave N is shut down at N Vincent Ave, N Upton Ave and N Morgan Ave.

-MoFmr4_2LXmQ-mhUX7s.text: Firefighters are taking caution of a propane tank inside the storage shed.

-MoFoBfkVLxVzhFB172e.text: Firefighters report have removed the propane tank from the shed. They advise they have doused most of the flames on the side of the shed.

-MoFogKHGhNHh6D0a6sF.text: Firefighters have discovered a trail of fire from the shed extending into the home through a vent.

-MoFqPA7S2pKQOtNoR7T.text: Firefighters are scouring the vents for any flames but only spot smoke disspating within the vents.

-MoFr95yT9cq_6HfaYuh.text: Firefighters are searching for possible hotspots on the second floor.

-MoFrWvh8gMrXZv5o45D.text: Firefighters confirm they have found an extension of the fire on a window on the second floor. They are hosing the flames down.

-MoFrfoVmQqyjn1epXZ0.text: Firefighters report they have contained the main body of the fire.

-MoFtyGWb4C_L53BVVma.text: Firefighters are still checking for extensions around the residence.

nib.text:
Seven people were displaced when a fire left a home in uninhabitable condition Thursday afternoon in Jordan.

Firefighters went to the house at North Upton Avenue near Lowry Avenue North around 2:30 p.m.

They found a shed fire extending to the two-story main house.

Surrounding streets were blocked as firefighters worked.

They were eventually able to put out the fire.

The fire department said the Red Cross was brought in to help three adults and four children who were displaced.

No injuries were reported.

The fires cause is being investigated.
